      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "Bug Fixes\r\n\r\n- Frontmatter merge no longer eats non-tag YAML lists. Previously, any list in your frontmatter (categories, authors, etc.) would be stripped during export. Now only the tags: block is removed and re-added via Obsidian's metadata. (#3 partial)\r\n- YAML list formatting normalised for Quarto. Both failure modes from #3 are fixed: single-quoted JSON arrays (resource-path: '[\"path\"]') and multiline YAML lists are now converted to the inline [\"path\"] format that Quarto and RStudio expect. (#3)\r\n- Image conversion no longer mangles embedded notes. The ![[...]] regex now only matches files with image/media extensions, so unresolved note embeds won't be turned into broken image syntax. Also handles Obsidian size hints (![[image.png|400]]).\r\n- Windows line endings handled correctly. Files with \\r\\n line endings are normalised at the start of conversion, fixing silent frontmatter detection failures for Windows users.\r\n\r\nNew Features\r\n\r\n- Wikilink conversion. [[Page Name]] and [[Page Name|Display Text]] are now converted to standard Markdown links with URL-encoded spaces.\r\n- Highlight syntax conversion. Obsidian's ==highlighted text== is converted to <mark> tags, which work in both HTML and PDF output.\r\n- Display math formatting. Single-line $$...$$ blocks are split to multi-line format for better readability in Quarto editors. (#5)\r\n\r\nHousekeeping\r\n\r\n- Removed unused slugify method\r\n- Improved callout content stripping (preserves indentation)",
